lead_paragraph: Under the watchful gaze of new coach and tennis royalty John McEnroe, sixth seed Milos Raonic got off to a solid start with a 7-6(4) 6-2 6-4 win over Spain's Pablo Carreno Busta at Wimbledon on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Raonic Up and Running as Big Mac Watches On
headline.main: Raonic Up and Running as Big Mac Watches On
